The following are the cocoa prices
paid in  Ivory Coast , the top producer, at the main growing
centers in the country from June 20 to June 26.  The national average paid was 610  CFA francs  ($1.34) per
kilogram (2.2 pounds). The highest average was 725 CFA francs
and the lowest 500 CFA francs.  Prices are in CFA francs per kilogram and the information
is from the countryâ€™s cocoa and coffee exchange, known as the
